# Derivation of the non-locality kernel from atomistic simulations
Atomistic simulations were used to test the heuristic arguments stated above. The non-locality kernel has been computed from the atomic level stress evaluated in a material subjected to a controlled deformation pattern. The exercise has been performed for a Morse material in which the interatomic interactions are described by a pair potential of the form, `\(u(r) = 4\left(e^{-4(x-1)} - e^{-2(x-1)}\right)\)` as well as for Al described by an EAM potential. The results are qualitatively similar and fully justify the observations made above. The kernel is long ranged and becomes negative beyond the first nearest neighbor. The kernels for Al are shown in Figure 2. Details of the procedure are to appear in J. Mech. Phys. Sol.

