# The Peierls-Nabarro model of a dislocation in non-local elasticity
The role of non-locality in the Peierls-Nabarro model was investigated and the results have been published in ({% cite picu_peierls_2002 %}).

First, the constitutive equation of the continuum (bounding the glide plane of the dislocation) was rendered non-local. The dislocation core becomes narrower with increasing the internal length scale of the model (mb), while the Peierls stress increases. Figure 3 shows the normalized core half-width as a function of the non-locality parameter m, while the corresponding normalized Peierls stress is shown in Figure 4. The Gaussian form (1) for the kernel was used in these calculations. 

